                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-70-victim689 t18300916-70-viclabel369"></join>. On the 7th of September, between nine and ten o'clock at night, I was at <placeName id="t18300916-70-crimeloc370">Bartholomew fair</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-70-crimeloc370" type="placeName" value="Bartholomew fair"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-70-crimeloc370" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-70-off367 t18300916-70-crimeloc370"></join>, and saw the prisoner in conversation with others; I felt somebody's hand at my coat pocket; I cast my eyes round, and saw the prisoner at my side - I caught hold of his hand, with my snuff-box in it; he had got it quite out of my pocket - I gave him in charge: I was not interrupted in securing him - I never saw him before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-70-person691">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PERCIVAL
